<p>The ratio of \(\frac{\text{ideas}}{\text{pages}}\) in the <a href="https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.06825.pdf">Mistral 7B</a> is too high. It combines efficiently all the techniques that are mentioned above. Additionally, they use:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Rolling buffer Cache:</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>Set the cache size to a value \(W\), and store the keys and values at step \(i\) at position \(i mod W\). Hence, starting from step \(W\), cache get overwritten with new values.</p>

<p>It doesn‚Äôt matter that much because we already use positional encoding!</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Pre-fill and Chunking:</strong></li>
</ul>

<p>I don‚Äôt get this yet. Check it later!</p>

<p>Of course it‚Äôs related to KV cache. 
Chunking: Split the prompt size in chunks of size \(W\) (window size of the attention)
